We recommended and the management agreed to:
Conduct proper monitoring of receipts and utilization of fund transfers from NGAs;
Evaluate the need for the unexpended fund balances from the Source Agencies and request authority to use the funds for other related projects, if warranted;
Instruct the heads or personnel in-charge of the Implementing Offices to immediately liquidate the fund transfers after the completion of the projects or once the purpose has been served; and
Immediately return any unutilized balances to the SAs in compliance with Item 3.1.2 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

Stop the procurement of goods and supplies for the requirement needs of the Municipality through cash advance, instead adhere to the proper procurement procedures under RA No. 9184 or the Procurement Law;

Abide by the regulation that all payments shall be paid by check except for small amounts which can be paid thru the Petty Cash Fund pursuant to the General Principle No. 2 under COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997;

Enforce the immediate liquidation of cash advances of the DO considering that the purposes of her advances have already been served;

Send demand letters in case of non-liquidation and enforce the withholding of salaries or other sanctions; and

Refrain from granting additional cash advance to Disbursing Officer with pending accountabilities.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

henceforth, ensure that the Municipality’s assets/properties are properly protected against possible loss and/or wastage by doing what an ordinary man with prudence and intelligence will do in managing and safeguarding its properties;

require the Municipal Accountant to properly recognize impairment loss when there are apparent indications that an impairment loss may have occurred in consonance with PPSAS 21;

require the members of the BAC and its Secretariat and TWG to henceforth, adhere to the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 conscientiously to promote good governance and taking into consideration the principle of transparency, accountability, equity, efficiency, and economy in all of the procurement process; and

instruct the Property Officer to notify the Audit Team within twenty-four (24) hours from acceptance of the items ordered, the time, date and place of delivery to give the Audit Team ample time in the conduct of inspection and verification of correctness thereof.

